            "questionText": "An astrophysicist is tracking a newly discovered asteroid with an estimated mass of $!$2 \\times 10^{12}\\text{ kilograms}$!$. As it passes close to Earth, it enters Earth's gravitational field, and the astrophysicist calculates the temporary increase in its weight due to Earth's pull to be $!$1.96 \\times 10^{13}\\text{ newtons}$!$. Gravitational field strength is defined as the force per unit mass. Based on these values, determine the gravitational field strength experienced by the asteroid in $!$\\text{N/kg}$!$.",
